    "body": "I can't reproduce the issue, being at epoch ~1300 and issued http://localhost:9596/validator/duties/3000/proposer to get proposer duties at epoch 3000, I got the log\r\n\r\n```\r\n2020-08-13 14:01:05  [API]             error: Request 4 failed with unexpected error:  Cannot get duties for epoch more than two ahead: 3000 <= 1302 Error: Cannot get duties for epoch more than two ahead: 3000 <= 1302\r\n    at Object.lte (/Users/tuyennguyen/Projects/workshop/lodestar/packages/lodestar-utils/lib/assert.js:40:13)\r\n    at ValidatorApi.getProposerDuties (/Users/tuyennguyen/Projects/workshop/lodestar/packages/lodestar/lib/api/impl/validator/validator.js:112:27)\r\n    at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:93:5)\r\n    at async Object.<anonymous> (/Users/tuyennguyen/Projects/workshop/lodestar/packages/lodestar/lib/api/rest/routes/validator/duties/proposer.js:27:27)\r\n```\r\n\r\nat browser side\r\n```\r\n{\"statusCode\":500,\"error\":\"Internal Server Error\",\"message\":\"Cannot get duties for epoch more than two ahead: 3000 <= 1302\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nso our node handles it pretty well with checking epoch before calling `processSlots` https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/api/impl/validator/validator.ts#L144",
